    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a potent core, anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.22) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.68), who represent our strongest offensive plays. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Bello and a significant boost from his elite BvP history, while **Jackson Merrill** leverages a high-leverage leadoff spot and a strong platoon advantage against Taillon. Furthermore, **Kyle Tucker** (73.24) and **Jacob Wilson** (72.73) provide high-floor production; **Jacob Wilson** specifically benefits from a 10% park factor bump and a high-leverage leadoff slot, making him a prime candidate to anchor our pursuit of categories beyond just raw power. **Josh Lowe** (72.21) remains an essential start, as his matchup against Fedde and his elite sprint speed\u2014vital for our stolen base-starved roster\u2014are further amplified by the pitcher's slow delivery to the plate.\n\nRegarding roster management, the optimizer faced a difficult decision at the utility spot, where **Marcell Ozuna** (61.53) narrowly edged out **Brady House** (44.40). While **Brady House** was in consideration, the lack of certainty in his lineup position combined with a negative platoon split against a lefty ultimately pushed him to the bench. Conversely, **Marcell Ozuna** benefits from favorable wind conditions and a solid platoon matchup, solidifying his role in the lineup. We are closely monitoring the weather in the **Heliot Ramos** (48.04) game, where a 40% rain risk could jeopardize his output; despite the favorable leadoff position, his efficiency is tempered by the prospect of an elite catcher\u2019s arm. Finally, we are forced to navigate the loss of **Gunnar Henderson**, who is unavailable today due to a confirmed rainout. We will keep **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Nolan Schanuel** on standby, ensuring we maintain roster flexibility should any of our projected starters like **Drake Baldwin**, **Nasim Nunez**, or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** receive late lineup scratches.",
